Reasoning: The paper proposes a new method for training restricted Boltzmann machines (RBM), which is a type of neural network commonly used in machine learning. The focus is on the optimization algorithm used to train the model, specifically the Frank-Wolfe algorithm. This makes the paper most likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, RBMs are often used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), so those sub-categories are also likely. The paper also mentions the use of RBMs in unsupervised feature learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE), which further supports these sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on image datasets, which suggests the Statistical Learning (cs.SD) sub-category as a possibility.
